<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:ns3="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="optimal" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>optimal</refname>
        <refpurpose>Optimal page replacement algorithm.</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>[faults] = optimal(no_frames, no_pages, ref_string, p)</synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
                <term>no_frames</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Number of frames.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>no_pages</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Number of pages.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
                <term>ref_string</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Page reference string in an array format.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
                <term>p</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The value of this determines whether to print the output or not(1/0).</para>
					<para>The default (optional parameter) value of this is 0.</para>
					<para>If the value is 0 it will only return otherwise it will print and return.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            
            <varlistentry>
                <term>faults</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Number of page faults.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>This function takes in the number of frames, number of pages and the reference string and returns the number of page faults using optimal page replacement algorithm.</para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example">[faults] = optimal(3, 7, [1, 3, 0, 3, 5, 6, 3], 1)</programlisting>
		<programlisting role="example">[faults] = optimal(3, 7, [1, 3, 0, 3, 5, 6, 3], 0)</programlisting>
    </refsection>
